    "name": "Panthereon",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Carefully constructed to serve as tomb guardians and protectors of their creators and their treasure, panthereons are a variant of clay golems. The majority of these golems were created during the First Age in Osirion, though evidence of their existence has turned up beyond the nation\u2019s borders. A panthereon stands over 8 feet tall and weighs 600 pounds. While its sculpted form may vary, it is typically muscular and wears no clothing save for a simple Osirian skirt."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>This finely sculpted statue is formed of hardened clay. Its muscular body is topped with the head of a feline predator.</i>",
